{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":40984,"name":"Eugene Kozlov","username":"Eugene","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/eugene/{size}/902_2.png","created_at":"2020-11-29T09:24:54.182Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eIâ€™m not asking how to use Urho networking in general.\u003cbr\u003e\nIâ€™m curious how you used Urho networking in your games in practice.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWhat API do you use? Do you use low-level messaging? Do you use remote events? Do you use scene replication? Please link the game if possible: itâ€™s important for the context.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI know only one multiplayer game made with Urho and they used 100% custom networing solution.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-11-29T09:24:54.182Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":4,"reads":46,"readers_count":45,"score":29.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":6582,"topic_slug":"how-do-you-use-urho-networking","display_username":"Eugene Kozlov","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Core developer","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":484,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":40985,"name":"é­”å¤§å†œ ğğğ³ ç¾æ‹›èœ","username":"Modanung","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/modanung/{size}/3290_2.png","created_at":"2020-11-29T09:56:43.879Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eNetworking - like UI - is low on my list of priorities for any project: It starts with a concept, from which graphics and gameplay grow together iteratively. Both networking and UI require most parts of a game to be somewhat set in stone. Iâ€™ve done some experiments, and what Urho provides seems to suffice for in-game purposes. However, \u003cem\u003eproperly\u003c/em\u003e testing its functionality is tricky without collaboration. \u003cspan class=\"spoiler\"\u003eSince I am only a single player.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOne thing that seems crucial yet not included with the engine is some form of matchmaking. Nobody wants to paste IPs around. And although I understand this to be somewhat out of scope for an \u003cem\u003eengine\u003c/em\u003e, it may be one of the reasons people use non-Urho solutions that \u003cem\u003edo\u003c/em\u003e come with this functionality. In my view however, these often seem somewhat bloated and dependent on centralized services. Someday I hope to use a database hosted on the LucKey Productions website to connect players through  in-game lobbies.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIâ€™ve also fantasized about having some protocol definition(s) that could associate links with games. These could then be sent or posted as a form of invitation. Something like magnet links for games.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-11-29T10:12:45.260Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":46,"readers_count":45,"score":64.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":6582,"topic_slug":"how-do-you-use-urho-networking","display_username":"é­”å¤§å†œ ğğğ³ ç¾æ‹›èœ","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":3,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":3}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":192,"hidden":false,"trust_level":0,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_suspended":true,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":40986,"name":"é­”å¤§å†œ ğğğ³ ç¾æ‹›èœ","username":"Modanung","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/modanung/{size}/3290_2.png","created_at":"2020-11-29T10:39:03.665Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eIt might also be nice to have something in-house akin to Steam/Battle.Net that could be used to browse/install available games (including prototypes), find other players, chat and start/share matches.\u003cbr\u003e\nAnd not be \u003ca href=\"https://spyware.neocities.org/articles/steam.html\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"\u003espyware\u003c/a\u003e of course, or provide any, for that matter. It might even come with the possibility of scheduling/announcing matches on a public \u003ca href=\"https://gitlab.com/Modanung/ChronoCal\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"\u003ecalendar\u003c/a\u003e. This could also be used for continuously adding new coop chapters on a regular basis, instead of thinking in terms of expansion packs.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-11-29T13:07:38.802Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":46,"readers_count":45,"score":9.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":6582,"topic_slug":"how-do-you-use-urho-networking","display_username":"é­”å¤§å†œ ğğğ³ ç¾æ‹›èœ","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":4,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://spyware.neocities.org/articles/steam.html","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Steam â€” Spyware Watchdog","clicks":1},{"url":"https://gitlab.com/Modanung/ChronoCal","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"é­”å¤§å†œ / ChronoCal Â· GitLab","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":192,"hidden":false,"trust_level":0,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_suspended":true,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":40987,"name":"é­”å¤§å†œ ğğğ³ ç¾æ‹›èœ","username":"Modanung","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/modanung/{size}/3290_2.png","created_at":"2020-11-29T10:54:43.263Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI see how core devs like to focus on the engine, but it helps to \u003cem\u003eunderstand\u003c/em\u003e weâ€™re inside an ecosystem.\u003cbr\u003e\nWithout a setting, youâ€™re just running isolated experiments, which - rightfully - \u003cem\u003eavoids\u003c/em\u003e complex relations.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-11-29T13:09:41.355Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":46,"readers_count":45,"score":9.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":6582,"topic_slug":"how-do-you-use-urho-networking","display_username":"é­”å¤§å†œ ğğğ³ ç¾æ‹›èœ","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":3,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":192,"hidden":false,"trust_level":0,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_suspended":true,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":41043,"name":"","username":"JSandusky","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/jsandusky/{size}/3220_2.png","created_at":"2020-12-01T02:52:15.592Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eSo nobody actually read the prompt.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI mostly used the lower level stuff, down to just interacting with CivetWeb itself for websockets and HTTP. HTTP for embedded debug-server, web-sockets for angelscript debugging.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIn a prototype that did use networking I also mostly relied on remote-events aside from the default replication. I really didnâ€™t care for the \u003ccode\u003eControls\u003c/code\u003e, it was needlessly limited and didnâ€™t bring anything for how limited it was (such as prediction or state tracking) - even for a prototype I ended up expanding that into something very very fat and then having to widdle it down before sending it off.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOnly 1 game (that is probably being played right now) Iâ€™ve made in Urho actually used networking, but it was done just before the SLikeNet move (it was the reason I did the initial RakNet work because kNet didnâ€™t have the guts needed for LAN discovery and adding it was going to be hell) and that also used mostly remote-events but \u003ccode\u003econtrols\u003c/code\u003e were less of a problem because it was targeted onto older generic Sega-based racing hardware for the Cape-verde arcade market. So it was really a LAN game as there was a hub machine with the local router and the other machines are plugged into that. So networking wasnâ€™t much of a hassle there since latency was almost a total non-issue.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIMO, the controls stuff is messed up. It doesnâ€™t make sense given that Urho3D doesnâ€™t really do much of anything fantastic regarding state. Itâ€™s not saving state, itâ€™s not rollback capable, itâ€™s just â€¦ \u003cem\u003emeh - hereâ€™s this packet of generic data where we decided some info is sort of important, have at it bro!\u003c/em\u003e Just make it a generic VariantMap then and add some basic delta capabilities to VariantMap.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-12-01T03:39:43.486Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":37,"readers_count":36,"score":117.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":6582,"topic_slug":"how-do-you-use-urho-networking","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"f